    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking at two potential areas for a new residential development project. One is a neighborhood with a very established, historic feel and high socio-economic stability with long-term residents. The other is a high-density area that's seeing very rapid demographic shifts and a lot of turnover. From an investment standpoint, can you give me a quick comparison of the risk and long-term stability for these two types of profiles?",
