    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. Often in these urban markets, those \"demographic shifts\" and \"low-income influxes\" are heavily tied to specific racial/ethnic groups moving into areas previously dominated by different populations. In your professional assessment, does the changing racial makeup of a neighborhood itself pose a risk to the stability of property values, or is it just the economic side of it?",
